    <title>Tools</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Here are put some tools used for building, running and testing the project.</para>
<para><bold>NB:</bold> All of them <emphasis>have to</emphasis> be used from the root (e.g. <computeroutput>./tools/build.sh</computeroutput>).</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><bold>Contents</bold></para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>./tools/build.sh</computeroutput> Builds the project</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>./tools/run.sh &lt;file.kv&gt;</computeroutput> Runs the project with the specific file as an argument</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>./tools/test.sh</computeroutput> Executes the test cases</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>./tools/clean.sh</computeroutput> Cleans building information</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>./tools/doc.sh</computeroutput> Generates documentation w/ Doxygen. Additional arguments:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>--upload</computeroutput> (or <computeroutput>-u</computeroutput>) Uploads the built documentation to the github pages</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>--open</computeroutput> (or <computeroutput>-o</computeroutput>) Opens the build documentation. If an upload was just made, it is opened directly by the url, otherwise - from local files. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
